The paper proposes a deep learning model for traffic prediction using spatio-temporal graph-based CNNs. The model involves learning expressive features to represent spatio-temporal structures and predict future traffic from historical traffic flow. This involves the use of graph-based spatio-temporal convolutional layers to extract features from a graph representation of traffic flow. The paper also discusses the use of graph prediction stream to predict the dynamic graph structures. Based on these aspects, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
